  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is foreign resident CGT withholding in Australia?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Foreign Resident Capital Gains Withholding (FRCGW) is an ATO regime where the buyer withholds 12.5% of the purchase price and pays it directly to the ATO on behalf of a foreign resident vendor. This is a prepayment against the vendor's potential CGT liability, not the final tax. The vendor then lodges an Australian tax return to determine the actual CGT owed, and any overpayment is refunded or the balance is payable at that point."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do I need a clearance certificate if I am an Australian resident selling my home?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. If you are an Australian tax resident, you should obtain a clearance certificate from the ATO before settlement. Without a clearance certificate, the buyer is legally required to withhold 12.5% of the purchase price regardless of your actual residency status. The clearance certificate confirms to the buyer that you are an Australian resident and that withholding is not required. The application is free and processed online through the ATO."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does CGT withholding affect the settlement process for foreign resident sellers?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "At settlement, the buyer's solicitor retains 12.5% of the purchase price and remits it to the ATO rather than paying the full proceeds to the vendor. The vendor receives the remaining 87.5%. The withheld amount is credited against the vendor's final CGT liability when they lodge their Australian tax return. This means the vendor's net proceeds at settlement are reduced, which can affect their ability to fund a simultaneous purchase or discharge a mortgage."
      }
    }
  ]
})}></script>

<article style="background:var(--color-surface-0);min-height:100vh;">

